Durban - A 32-year-old man was stabbed multiple times in Avoca on Tuesday. It is believed that the man and a colleague were working at the Avoca railway station when they were approached by a man carrying a screwdriver. 

Marshall Security spokesperson, Kyle van Reenen, said the assailant then robbed the workers before turning to stab one of the men with the screwdriver. 
"The victim was treated and stabilised at the scene by advanced life support paramedics before being taken to hospital for further care," he said. ADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads

In a separate incident, a 21-year-old woman was stabbed in front of her toddler in Verulam earlier in the day. 
Reaction Unit SA spokesperson, Prem Balram, said woman's body was spotted by a passing motorist.

"Medics attempted to resuscitate the woman but she died at the scene. Her 2-year-old child, who was seated on top of her body, had to be removed by officers.The woman's husband said they were walking home when they were accosted by two men who robbed the woman of her phone. The husband said one of the suspects stabbed the woman in her back. The two suspects fled," Balram said. 
Police are investigating both incidents. 
The Mercury